<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-11-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-11-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="140" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d140">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6775/236.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of Salvador</gloss>
                                to President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        Salvador</hi></placeName>,<lb/>(Received <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-11-19">November 19,
                                1907</date>.)</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I have the honor to inform Your Excellency that peace and tranquillity
                            having been restored throughout the country, the constitutional path was
                            entered this day, the state of siege raised, and absolute and
                            unconditional amnesty granted to cover all political offenses.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">F. Figueroa.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>